[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1270},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F26\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F26\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F26\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F26\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer\u002F":1246,"related:\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2025\u002F09\u002F26\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer\u002F":1255},"\u002Flearnexp\u002F20250926\u002F1972102857\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1225,"date":1226,"description":1227,"extension":1228,"lang":1229,"meta":1230,"navigation":325,"path":1231,"readingMinutes":1232,"seo":1233,"standalone":1234,"stem":1235,"tags":1236,"tldr":1242,"updated":1243,"url":1244,"__hash__":1245},"content\u002Fen\u002FLearning\u002Fday-26-forced-to-become-a-frontend-engineer.md","【Day 26】And Just Like That, I Was Forced into Becoming a Frontend Engineer","1972028571",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1219},"minimark",[11,30,37,41,44,47,50,53,61,64,67,70,78,81,92,117,120,123,126,129,132,135,150,163,166,169,172,178,181,185,188,191,194,200,203,209,212,215,218,221,228,231,238,241,244,247,961,964,967,976,979,1061,1072,1075,1088,1091,1094,1110,1113,1125,1128,1134,1154,1157,1161,1164,1168,1171,1215],[12,13,14],"blockquote",{},[15,16,17,21,22,29],"p",{},[18,19,20],"strong",{},"Warning","\nThis series has been rewritten and published as a book, currently available at ",[23,24,28],"a",{"href":25,"rel":26},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.tenlong.com.tw\u002Fproducts\u002F9786267889251?list_name=i-r-zh_tw",[27],"nofollow","Tenlong Bookstore"," (in Traditional Chinese). (Updated 2026\u002F05\u002F07)\nThe book version was essentially rewritten from scratch — I filled in the parts of the story I couldn't fully tell during the original IT Home serialization, and cleaned up sections where the writing wasn't precise enough. It's a version I'm much happier with.\nIf you enjoy this post and want more, or want the polished version, the book is the way to go. The blog and IT Home will keep the original serialized version for archive purposes — please treat the book as the authoritative reference.",[15,31,32],{},[33,34],"img",{"alt":35,"src":36},"And just like that, I was forced into becoming a frontend engineer","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Flearnexp\u002Fithelp-2025\u002Fday26\u002FChatGPT%20Image%202025%E5%B9%B49%E6%9C%8820%E6%97%A5%20%E4%B8%8B%E5%8D%8810_08_47.png",[38,39,35],"h2",{"id":40},"and-just-like-that-i-was-forced-into-becoming-a-frontend-engineer",[15,42,43],{},"You read that right — due to company needs, I got dragged from PHP into being a frontend engineer.",[15,45,46],{},"Reason? Because I was the only one in the company who'd touched HTML & CSS. So my manager's brain logic went:",[15,48,49],{},"knows how to slice → knows frontend → must know JavaScript",[15,51,52],{},"So I got shoved onto the frontend path of no return XD.",[12,54,55],{},[15,56,57,60],{},[18,58,59],{},"Note","\nBrowsers use HTML to structure web content, CSS to style appearance, and JavaScript to add interactivity and dynamic effects. These three complement each other and together form the foundation of modern web pages.",[15,62,63],{},"Don't ask why I was so compliant. After touching HTML and CSS, it was like a new world opened up — I got really into frontend dev.",[15,65,66],{},"So when my manager pushed, I just fell into the pit and became a frontend engineer.",[15,68,69],{},"Daily office dialogue was something like:",[15,71,72,73,77],{},"\"Ray, how do you use ",[74,75,76],"code",{},"position: absolute;","?\"",[15,79,80],{},"\"Ray, can you fix the company homepage?\"",[15,82,83,84,87,88,91],{},"\"Ray, why does this ",[74,85,86],{},"Button"," inside a ",[74,89,90],{},"Form"," submit the form when clicked?\"",[12,93,94],{},[15,95,96,98,99,102,103,106,107,110,111,116],{},[18,97,59],{},"\nButtons inside ",[74,100,101],{},"\u003Cform>"," default to submitting the form. To avoid this, set the ",[74,104,105],{},"type"," attribute to ",[74,108,109],{},"button",". See \"",[23,112,115],{"href":113,"rel":114},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fhtml\u002F20220924\u002F1348879561\u002F",[27],"The Weird Type Phenomenon with Button","\" (article in Mandarin) for details.",[15,118,119],{},"Anything frontend-related → ask Ray.",[15,121,122],{},"Ray = Frontend.",[15,124,125],{},"\"Ray, here's some JavaScript — can you take a look?\"\nOne day, my manager dropped this on me.",[15,127,128],{},"My first internal reaction:\n\"Huh? I don't know JS either!\" 🤯",[15,130,131],{},"But outwardly you have to fake professionalism, nodding \"OK, I'll take a look.\" (Then secretly flipping through the manual XD.)",[15,133,134],{},"Luckily the code wasn't hard — basic DOM manipulation and event handling. I was relieved: \"Phew, not too brutal — heaven smiled upon me XD.\"",[15,136,137,138,143,144,149],{},"This also led me to buy another course from the team that did ",[23,139,142],{"href":140,"rel":141},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fcourse\u002Fhtml-css-learning\u002F",[27],"Build a Website with HTML and CSS",": ",[23,145,148],{"href":146,"rel":147},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.hexschool.com\u002Fcourses\u002Fjavascript.html",[27],"JavaScript Intro - Apprentice's Trial",". That's when I really got to know HexSchool.",[12,151,152],{},[15,153,154,156,157,162],{},[18,155,59],{},"\n\"JavaScript Intro - Apprentice's Trial\" has since been replaced by a newer course. Consider checking ",[23,158,161],{"href":159,"rel":160},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.hexschool.com\u002Fcourses\u002Fjs-plus.html",[27],"JavaScript Essentials - Full Frontend Strategy",".",[15,164,165],{},"Not long after, my manager started prepping a new project and muttered to himself: \"Maybe we'll try Vue.js for the next project.\"",[15,167,168],{},"My internal monologue: \"Crap, I'm being forced to upgrade to new skills.\"",[15,170,171],{},"So I just went all-in and bought the HexSchool frontend bundle and started grinding.",[15,173,174],{},[33,175],{"alt":176,"src":177},"Frontend bundle","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Flearnexp\u002Fithelp-2025\u002Fday25\u002F20250920144501.png",[15,179,180],{},"And that's how I started my frontend engineer journey.",[38,182,184],{"id":183},"javascript-basics","JavaScript basics",[15,186,187],{},"Compared to C, JavaScript is easier to learn and brings satisfaction faster. \"Satisfaction\" here means: paired with HTML and CSS, you can immediately see results on screen.",[15,189,190],{},"\"Why?\" you might wonder.",[15,192,193],{},"C, C++, etc. require more complex dev environments and more interaction through CLIs (Command Line Interfaces). For beginners, that can feel dry.",[15,195,196],{},[33,197],{"alt":198,"src":199},"Terminal (example)","https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fmaster\u002Fassets\u002Fimages\u002Ftyped_8encjeq.gif",[15,201,202],{},"In the early years of the web, pages were very static. How static? Here's an early YouTube example.",[15,204,205],{},[33,206],{"alt":207,"src":208},"YouTube 2005 (source: web)","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Flearnexp\u002Fithelp-2025\u002Fday26\u002Fyoutube-2005.png",[15,210,211],{},"Few visual elements — mostly text. Images were possible but it was still very static.",[15,213,214],{},"Pages were mostly structured with HTML and beautified with CSS. Looked better, but still lacked interactivity.",[15,216,217],{},"\"Interactivity? You mean CSS animations?\" you might think.",[15,219,220],{},"Here \"interactivity\" doesn't mean pretty visuals — it means users can interact with the page. Clicking buttons, filling forms, getting immediate response or feedback — like form validation or dynamic content updates.",[15,222,223,224,227],{},"CSS at the time could only provide visual effects, not true interactivity. The key was JavaScript — even called the \"",[18,225,226],{},"Glue Language","\" back then.",[15,229,230],{},"What's a glue language?",[15,232,233,234,237],{},"In short, a language that ",[18,235,236],{},"\"glues together\""," different technologies or systems.",[15,239,240],{},"For JavaScript, it glues HTML and CSS, making pages no longer just static but interactive.",[15,242,243],{},"Early on, JavaScript's main role was providing interaction. By now, its scope has expanded enormously — frontend, server-side, desktop apps, mobile apps — basically a fully general-purpose language.",[15,245,246],{},"We said JavaScript is relatively easy. How easy? Quick example:",[248,249,254],"pre",{"className":250,"code":251,"language":252,"meta":253,"style":253},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u002F\u002F Declare variables\nvar message = \"Hello, World!\";\nlet number = 42;\nconst pi = 3.14;\n\n\u002F\u002F Output variables\n\u002F\u002F console.log outputs content to the console\nconsole.log(message);\nconsole.log(number);\nconsole.log(pi);\n\n\u002F\u002F Conditional\nif (number > 0) {\n    console.log(\"This is a positive number\");\n} else {\n    console.log(\"Not a positive number\");\n}\n\n\u002F\u002F Loop\nfor (let i = 0; i \u003C 5; i++) {\n    console.log(\"This is iteration \" + i);\n}\n\n\u002F\u002F Array\nlet fruits = [\"Apple\", \"Banana\", \"Orange\"];\nfruits.forEach(function(fruit) {\n    console.log(\"I like eating \" + fruit);\n});\n\n\u002F\u002F Function\nfunction greet(name) {\n    return \"Hi, \" + name + \"!\";\n}\nconsole.log(greet(\"Ray\"));\n\n\u002F\u002F OOP\nclass Person {\n    constructor(name, age) {\n        this.name = name;\n        this.age = age;\n    }\n\n    introduce() {\n        return \"My name is \" + this.name + \", I'm \" + this.age + \" years old.\";\n    }\n}\nlet person = new Person(\"Ray\", 30);\nconsole.log(person.introduce());\n\n\u002F\u002F Exception handling\ntry {\n    let result = number \u002F 0; \u002F\u002F Produces Infinity\n    console.log(result);\n} catch (error) {\n    console.error(\"Error: \" + error.message);\n} finally {\n    console.log(\"Program execution finished\");\n}\n","js","",[74,255,256,265,286,303,320,327,333,339,352,362,372,377,383,401,418,430,444,450,455,461,496,514,519,524,530,560,582,599,605,610,616,631,653,658,678,683,689,700,717,731,744,750,755,764,798,803,808,834,850,855,861,869,893,903,914,932,942,956],{"__ignoreMap":253},[257,258,261],"span",{"class":259,"line":260},"line",1,[257,262,264],{"class":263},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F Declare variables\n",[257,266,268,272,276,279,283],{"class":259,"line":267},2,[257,269,271],{"class":270},"sWyjQ","var",[257,273,275],{"class":274},"sMAXC"," message ",[257,277,278],{"class":270},"=",[257,280,282],{"class":281},"sTRMh"," \"Hello, World!\"",[257,284,285],{"class":274},";\n",[257,287,289,292,295,297,301],{"class":259,"line":288},3,[257,290,291],{"class":270},"let",[257,293,294],{"class":274}," number ",[257,296,278],{"class":270},[257,298,300],{"class":299},"sCcAr"," 42",[257,302,285],{"class":274},[257,304,306,309,312,315,318],{"class":259,"line":305},4,[257,307,308],{"class":270},"const",[257,310,311],{"class":299}," pi",[257,313,314],{"class":270}," =",[257,316,317],{"class":299}," 3.14",[257,319,285],{"class":274},[257,321,323],{"class":259,"line":322},5,[257,324,326],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":325},true,"\n",[257,328,330],{"class":259,"line":329},6,[257,331,332],{"class":263},"\u002F\u002F Output variables\n",[257,334,336],{"class":259,"line":335},7,[257,337,338],{"class":263},"\u002F\u002F console.log outputs content to the console\n",[257,340,342,345,349],{"class":259,"line":341},8,[257,343,344],{"class":274},"console.",[257,346,348],{"class":347},"sj_SG","log",[257,350,351],{"class":274},"(message);\n",[257,353,355,357,359],{"class":259,"line":354},9,[257,356,34